The paper deals with the correctness of concurrent objects, which is a topic in the area of concurrent programming. The paper specifically focuses on the links between safety and progress properties of concurrent objects and a form of trace refinement for client programs, called contextual trace refinement. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
